"v. 调制；捏造 【英】 v. 调制，捏造 (to make by combining various ingredients) 【记】 con＋coct=cook(烹调 )→调制 【同】 派生词: concoction (n. 调配[物]，谎言) 【例】 John concocted an excuse for being late. v. (把调料混合在一起)调制; 捏造(谎言) 【例】I concocted an excuse for being late 我编造了一个迟到的籍口. 【记】con共同, coct = cook(v 烹调)－调制 【参】concoction(n 调配物; 谎言) 【记】源自cook， (把东西弄到)一起cook → 混合调制；cocktail 调制鸡尾酒 【相关】decoct 熬，把水煮沸取之精华； concoct (v.)  1530s, ""to digest,"" from Latin concoctus, past participle of concoquere ""to digest; to boil together, prepare; to consider well,"" from com- ""together"" (see com-) + coquere ""to cook"" (see cook (n.)). Meaning ""to prepare an edible thing"" is from 1670s. First expanded metaphorically beyond cooking 1792. Related: Concocted; concocting."
